Message.SourceString: Ah, I see you've discovered Ashenfall's little "blacksmith benefit", as I like to call it. Lifeward!
Message.LocalizedString: Ah, I see you've discovered Ashenfall's little "blacksmith benefit", as I like to call it. Lifeward!

Message.SourceString: Crafting certain equipment intrinsically involves the weaving of small threads of enchantment, granting you greater protection.
Message.LocalizedString: Crafting certain equipment intrinsically involves the weaving of small threads of enchantment, granting you greater protection.

Message.SourceString: Go and craft a wardstone and bring it here so I can check your working. You just need to gather some rune essence and stone, and craft them at a rune altar. Nice and simple. One wardstone will do.
Message.LocalizedString: Go and craft a wardstone and bring it here so I can check your working. You just need to gather some rune essence and stone, and craft them at a rune altar. Nice and simple. One wardstone will do.

Message.SourceString: Ah, you've made one. Lovely. See, that barely hurt at all. Just a little drop of blood, nothing to cry about. But now, when your lifeward is damaged, you can repair it.
Message.LocalizedString: Ah, you've made one. Lovely. See, that barely hurt at all. Just a little drop of blood, nothing to cry about. But now, when your lifeward is damaged, you can repair it.

Message.SourceString: Handy stuff, especially with dragons about. Now, you'll find that your Lifewards can get depleted by the brutality of the other creatures on Ashenfall.
Message.LocalizedString: Handy stuff, especially with dragons about. Now, you'll find that your Lifewards can get depleted by the brutality of the other creatures on Ashenfall.

Message.SourceString: To recharge them, you'll need to craft yourself wardstones. These impressive little doohickies will recharge the Lifeward enchantments on your armour... at a small cost.
Message.LocalizedString: To recharge them, you'll need to craft yourself wardstones. These impressive little doohickies will recharge the Lifeward enchantments on your armour... at a small cost.

Message.SourceString: A bit of damage to your soul. Don't worry, it's not permanent, but perhaps avoid overindulging in Wardstones, eh?
Message.LocalizedString: A bit of damage to your soul. Don't worry, it's not permanent, but perhaps avoid overindulging in Wardstones, eh?

Message.SourceString: Just use a wardstone and BAM! Instant Lifeward recharge. Sure, it'll tear a bit out of your soul, but so will listening to Doric talk about hammers for three hours.
Message.LocalizedString: Just use a wardstone and BAM! Instant Lifeward recharge. Sure, it'll tear a bit out of your soul, but so will listening to Doric talk about hammers for three hours.

Message.SourceString: Just don't use too many at once, and you'll be fine. Right, go on, get out there and slay that dragon!
Message.LocalizedString: Just don't use too many at once, and you'll be fine. Right, go on, get out there and slay that dragon!

Message.SourceString: Hrmm, I have something for you, but it appears you've overloaded yourself like a magpie gone mad. Clear some space, then come and see me.
Message.LocalizedString: Hrmm, I have something for you, but it appears you've overloaded yourself like a magpie gone mad. Clear some space, then come and see me.

Message.SourceString: Go and craft me one small wardstone and bring it here so I can check your working. You just need to gather some rune essence and stone, and craft it at a rune altar. Nice and simple. One small wardstone will do.
Message.LocalizedString: Go and craft me one small wardstone and bring it here so I can check your working. You just need to gather some rune essence and stone, and craft it at a rune altar. Nice and simple. One small wardstone will do.
